{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/py-input","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"0b01acb4-44d0-5032-9f38-f327b5c30394","html":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#syntax\">Syntax</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#application\">Application</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#related\">Related</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Reading user input is an important part of a program. To collect user input from the terminal in Python, we use the input() method. To store user input to a variable, use ’variable = input()’</p>\n<h2 id=\"syntax\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#syntax\" aria-label=\"syntax permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Syntax</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\">anyVar <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">input</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>inputQuestion<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Most of the time, user input needs to be stored in a variable to be read in the future.</p>\n<p>The input() method can take in 1 string as a parameter. That string can count as the question the program asks before retrieving input.</p>\n<h2 id=\"application\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#application\" aria-label=\"application permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Application</h2>\n<p>As an example we will make an application that asks 2 numbers from the user and adds them.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Input two numbers\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\nnumber1 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">input</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"First number: \"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\nnumber2 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">input</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Second number: \"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\nanswer <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> number1 <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> number2\n<span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>answer<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Output:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">Input two numbers\nFirst number: 2\nSecond number: 3\n5</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"related\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#related\" aria-label=\"related permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Related:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/posts/py-installation\">Python - Installation Hello World</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/posts/py-variables\">Python - Variables</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/posts/py-for-loop\">Python - For Loops</a></li>\n</ul>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/py-input","tagSlugs":["/tag/python/","/tag/tutorial/","/tag/input/","/tag/output/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-10-18T16:25:03+08:00","description":"Reading user input is an important part of a program. To collect user input from the terminal in Python, we use the input() method. To store user input to a variable, use 'variable = input()'","tags":["Python","Tutorial","Input","Output"],"title":"Python Input","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/py-input"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","3942705351","401334301"]}